[
    {
        "content": "<p>We seem to lack the following.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LE</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">IsPreorder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Total</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"o\">)]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">IsLinearPreorder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">le_total</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Total</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">total</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Min</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LE</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">LawfulOrderMin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Refl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"o\">)]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Total</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">total</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">LawfulOrderInf</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">le_min_iff</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">LawfulOrderInf</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">le_min_iff</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">MinEqOr</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">min_eq_or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Refl</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">refl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Refl</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">refl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">grind</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This allows one to infer as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Min</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LE</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">LawfulOrderMin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">IsPreorder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">IsLinearPreorder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inferInstance</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This inference is stated in the docstring for <code>Std.LawfulOrderMin</code> but - as far as I can tell - never actually proved. Would these be a welcome PR?</p>",
        "id": 558454935,
        "sender_full_name": "Wrenna Robson",
        "timestamp": 1763651389
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, in Mathlib, we appear to be missing these:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LinearOrder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">LawfulOrderLeftLeaningMax</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">max_eq_left</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">grind</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">max_eq_right</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">grind</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LinearOrder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">LawfulOrderLeftLeaningMin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">min_eq_left</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">grind</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">min_eq_right</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">grind</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>which then gives:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LinearOrder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">LawfulOrderSup</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inferInstance</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LinearOrder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">LawfulOrderInf</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inferInstance</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>which we also don't have (but can infer from this).</p>",
        "id": 558484827,
        "sender_full_name": "Wrenna Robson",
        "timestamp": 1763658286
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is a particularly odd one to me: we don't seem to have this instance registered but nothing actually seems needed to do so:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LinearOrder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">LawfulOrd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 558487735,
        "sender_full_name": "Wrenna Robson",
        "timestamp": 1763659117
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks for your thoughtful proposal!</p>\n<p>I omitted the first ones deliberately from the standard library. Automatically assembling weak instances into strong ones has its problems -- even for <code>Prop</code>-valued classes, I try to minimize the number of loops in the typeclass graph as I found performance to be sensitive to such changes. If a type is a linear order, <code>IsLinearOrder</code> needs to be provided explicitly, just like it is the case for <code>LinearOrder</code> in Mathlib.</p>\n<p>Note that <code>IsTotalPreorder.of_le</code> is already able to create the first instance you proposed:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">public</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IsLinearPreorder</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">of_isPreorder_of_total</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LE</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">IsPreorder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Total</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"o\">)]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IsLinearPreorder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">of_le</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>With regard to the second, I'm sure there are lots of fine-grained hypotheses that imply some other low-level instance, but as long as there is no evidence of such a lemma being very profitable in actual code, I don't want to add all of this type class inference complexity to the library. I found type class inference to be a bad fit for multidirectional logical reasoning. When possible, the high-level typeclasses should be used and the API is optimized for that (and could be optimized further, perhaps).</p>\n<p>Thanks for pointing out <code>Std.LawfulOrderMin</code>'s docstring. I wanted to describe how that class <em>logically</em> relates to the others, but I should clarify that there is no instance for it. As written, it really sounds like there is an instance. I do think that a plain theorem would make sense for that, though.</p>",
        "id": 558496324,
        "sender_full_name": "Paul Reichert",
        "timestamp": 1763661687
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thank you for the feedback. It's very much appreciated. Honestly the thing I find most confusing is the different approaches between Mathlib and Std to the order hierarchy - bundled or unbundled - which reaches its zenith with LinearOrder (which is like it is for a good reason, mind - and unbundling it seems an intimidating task).</p>",
        "id": 558496924,
        "sender_full_name": "Wrenna Robson",
        "timestamp": 1763661884
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If an instance wasn't intended, then I do agree that the docstring could well be altered (and as you say perhaps one could have a theorem). I just want to make sure I'm writing theorems that are as tight as possible (that is, do not contain redundant assumptions). That's I think why I end up lower level than is perhaps intended.</p>",
        "id": 558497456,
        "sender_full_name": "Wrenna Robson",
        "timestamp": 1763662051
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The reason why <code>Std</code> takes a different approach than Mathlib is that the use cases are different. When writing programs, having good control over the data-carrying syntactical classes (<code>LE</code>, <code>LT</code>, <code>Min</code>, <code>Ord</code>, <code>DecidableLE</code>, ...) is important for efficiency, and it should be convenient to provide a linear order on whatever subset of these has been implemented -- without automatically providing inefficient implementations of the other ones. By unbundling, we promise ourselves more flexibility in this regard.</p>",
        "id": 558500911,
        "sender_full_name": "Paul Reichert",
        "timestamp": 1763663075
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That makes sense - I just often find myself wanting to do reasoning of a style that is more program-y but that needs to dip into MathLib.</p>",
        "id": 558513773,
        "sender_full_name": "Wrenna Robson",
        "timestamp": 1763667388
    }
]